\c 67
\p
\v 1 For the music director; with music; a psalm; a song.
\q1
\v 2 May God be gracious to us and bless us
\q1 May he cause his face to shine upon us\f + \ft Selah\f*
\q1
\v 3 That your ways may be known in the earth
\q1 Your salvation among all nations
\q1
\v 4 Let the peoples praise you, O God
\q1 Let the peoples, all of them, praise you
\q1
\v 5 Let the peoples be glad and shout for joy
\q1 For you will judge the peoples with uprightness
\q1 And the peoples on earth you will guide
\q1
\v 6 Let the peoples praise you, O God
\q1 Let the peoples, all of them, praise you.
\q1
\v 7 The land has given its produce
\q1 God, our God, blesses us
\q1
\v 8 God blesses us
\q1 May they fear him,
\q1 All the ends of the earth.